<TITLE> HC rules national mourning day be restored </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 27 (bdnews24.com)A High Court ruling on Sunday entails August 15, the day of Sheikh Mujibur Rahman's assassination in 1975, be restored as national mourning day and a public holiday. In its ruling, a High Court bench overturned the past BNP-led government's move to cancel the country's national mourning day. bd
